{"ID":270323, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"323\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs322.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs324.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 323<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">Son of Man;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> so Melchizedek ordained Abraham<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and sent him away. Abraham rejoiced, saying,\n  Now I have a priesthood.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Mission of Elijah<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Salvation<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> could not come to the world without the mediation of Jesus Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">How shall God come to the rescue<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> of this generation? He will send Elijah the prophet.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> The law\n  revealed to Moses in Horeb never was revealed to the children of Israel as a nation.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> Elijah shall\n  reveal the covenants<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> to seal the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the children to the fathers.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The anointing and sealing is to be called, elected and made sure.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">&ldquo;Without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning of days nor end of\n  life, but made like unto the Son of God, abideth a priest continually.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> The Melchizedek Priesthood\n  holds the right from the eternal God,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and not by descent from father and mother; and that\n  priesthood is as eternal<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> as God Himself,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> having neither beginning of days nor end of life.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The 2nd Priesthood is Patriarchal authority.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> Go to and finish the temple, and God will fill it\n  with power,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and you will then receive more knowledge concerning this priesthood.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The 3rd is what is called the Levitical Priesthood, consisting of priests to administer in outward\n  ordinances,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> made without an oath; but the Priesthood of Melchizedek is by an oath and covenant.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The Holy Ghost is God&rsquo;s messenger<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> to administer in all those priesthoods.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Jesus Christ is the heir of this Kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span>&mdash;the Only Begotten of the Father<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> according to the\n  flesh,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> and holds the keys over all this world.<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Men have to suffer that they may come upon Mount Zion<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and be exalted above the heavens.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I know a man that has been caught up to the third heavens,<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> and can say, with Paul, that we\n  have seen and heard things that are not lawful to utter.<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> (Aug. 27, 1843.) DHC 5:554-556.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Instructions Respecting Plurality of Wives<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">In the afternoon, rode to the prairie to show some of the brethren some land. Evening, at home,\n  and walked up and<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108216\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108216)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108216)\">Matt. 24:27,37,39<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113853\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113853)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113853)\">D&amp;C 45:39<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116911\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116911)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116911)\">Moses 7:47,65<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114615\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114615)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114615)\">D&amp;C 84:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111542\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111542)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111542)\">Mosiah 3:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111616\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111616)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111616)\">Mosiah 13:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109992\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109992)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109992)\">1 Tim. 2:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110229\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110229)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110229)\">Heb. 8:6<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110233\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110233)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110233)\">Heb. 9:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110325\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110325)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110325)\">Heb. 12:24<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111109\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111109)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111109)\">2 Ne. 2:27-28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" i